    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-members/sap-build-apps-customize-standard-table-part-1/bc-p/13891866#M169645</id>
    <title>Re: SAP Build Apps - Customize Standard Table Part 1</title>
    <updated>2024-10-08T08:56:30.403000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;It is really nice blog, and good to learn about customizing components, and specifically how the table component works.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;But I think this is generally too complicated to be worthwhile for most developers of any type using this no-code SAP Build Apps. Strangely, the thing that annoys me the most is that you have to create the delete icon and logic twice (though you can simplify it with custom events). I personally think at this point it is best to create your own table control, which is pretty easy using containers and styling. I believe soon SAP Build Apps will provide templates for such things.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;See this Devtoberfest session:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;div class="video-embed-center video-embed"&gt;&lt;iframe class="embedly-embed" src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F4zVepzBgSmM%3Ffeature%3Doembed&amp;amp;display_name=YouTube&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D4zVepzBgSmM&amp;amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2F4zVepzBgSmM%2Fhqdefault.jpg&amp;amp;key=b0d40caa4f094c68be7c29880b16f56e&amp;amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;amp;schema=youtube" width="200" height="112" scrolling="no" title="🟣 Develop Even Faster (!) with SAP Build Apps Templates" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture;" allowfullscreen="true"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-members/sap-build-apps-customize-standard-table-part-1/bc-p/13891866#M169645"/>
    <published>2024-10-08T08:56:30.403000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
