    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Sorry for the delay in responding ... you know Devtoberfest and TechEd and all that &lt;span class="lia-unicode-emoji" title=":face_with_open_mouth:"&gt;😮&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Can you expand on your question? You want to have on-device storage but to have 2 entities, one with primary key and another with a field that references the PK in the first entity? There is no intrinsic relationships for individual entities, but of course you can design the app to use a field in one entity to hold primary keys from another entity. But you can define your own primary key -- you can just use the default ID&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
