      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Just create a custom script.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Input of type Any&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Output of type Any&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;And then the code is just:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-javascript"&gt;&lt;code&gt;return myInput.inputs[0].d.results[0].QuantityInBaseUnit;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;P&gt;You'll of course have to bind the output of the Call Web Service to the custom script.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;But all of this is if you want to store it in a variable. You don't need a custom script because you can use the expression editor to get the value you want directly (below is me using the root of Northwind service to get name of the first entity):&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1728397492579.png" style="width: 692px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/177130i8C285BC4A23B3691/image-dimensions/692x495?v=v2" width="692" height="495" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1728397492579.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1728397492579.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-how-to-resolve-resnponse-from-a-web-service-call-in-a/qaq-p/13892805/comment-id/4887362#M4887362"/>
    <published>2024-10-08T16:25:31.473000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
